sation and spontaneity that profoundly influenced poetry, music, and politics. By examining the culture of improvisation, this book reveals the ways in which Renaissance thinkers transcended cultural dichotomies, both in theory and in practice. Drawing on a wide range of sources, including letters, poetry, visual art, and philosophical texts, A Sudden Frenzy reveals the far-reaching and sometimes surprising ways that these phenomena shaped cultural developments in the Italian Renaissance and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFolk poetry, ItalianxHistory and criticism. 0aHumanismzItaly. 0aImprovisation (Music)xHistoryy15th century. 0aItalian poetryy15th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPerformance poetryzItalyxHistory and criticism. 0aRenaissancezItaly. 0aVocal musiczItalyy15th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aAngelo Poliziano.  aFlorence.  aItalian art.  aItalian literature.  aItaly.  aLorenzo de’ Medici.  aMarsilio Ficino.  aRenaissance literature.  aculture of improvisation.  ahumanism.  aimprovisation.  aorality.  apoetry.  apower.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148756345540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487563455423Coveruhttps://www.degru